<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871127-0065 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:SHL Systemhouse Inc.</HL><DD> 11/27/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> SHKIFDOW JONES INTERVIEW (CEO) </IN><TEXT>   SHL Systemhouse Inc. should report a 50% net income increase and a 75% to 80% revenue rise for the fiscal first quarter ending Monday, said Roderick M. Bryden, chairman and chief executive officer.    In the year-ago quarter, the Ottawa-based systems integration concern earned 4.31 million Canadian dollars ($3.28 million), or 18 cents a share, on revenue of 33.8 million dollars.    For the full year, Mr. Bryden expects net ranging from 1.30 dollars to 1.40 dollars a share on revenue ranging from 275 million dollars to 300 million dollars. For fiscal 1987, earnings were 23.8 million dollars, or 93 cents a share, on revenue of 176.2 million dollars.    The company plans to spend about 90 million dollars on acquisitions this year to improve its position in markets where it already operates. Chicago, Quebec province and the West Coast are viewed as priority markets, Mr. Bryden said.    Mr. Bryden owns about 32% of Systemhouse through his closely held Kinburn Technology Corp. </TEXT></DOC>